The paper deals with storage systems and their limitations, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses lower bounds for wait-free emulations, which is a topic in Distributed Systems (cs.DS). The use of coding techniques in storage systems is a topic in Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the limitations of non-authenticated storage systems, which is a topic in Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the emulation of shared registers, which is a topic in Control and Systems Theory (cs.SY).
